---
title: calc_excess_blob_gas (EIP-7918)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init
    q_init --> q_compute_target : target_blob_gas = GAS_PER_BLOB * blobSchedule.target
    q_compute_target --> q_check_underflow : excess + blob_gas_used < target_blob_gas
    q_compute_target --> q_check_reserve : excess + blob_gas_used >= target_blob_gas
    q_check_underflow --> q_final : return 0
    q_check_reserve --> q_exec_led : BLOB_BASE_COST * base_fee > GAS_PER_BLOB * blob_base_fee
    q_check_reserve --> q_blob_led : BLOB_BASE_COST * base_fee <= GAS_PER_BLOB * blob_base_fee
    q_exec_led --> q_final : return excess + blob_gas_used * (max - target) / max
    q_blob_led --> q_final : return excess + blob_gas_used - target_blob_gas
    q_final --> [*]

    note right of q_check_reserve
        INV-001: calc_excess_blob_gas always returns a non-negative integer
        INV-002: When total gas below target, excess resets to 0
        INV-003: In exec-fee-led regime, excess never decreases
        INV-004: Max per-block increase bounded by used * (max-target)/max
    end note
